* sysvinit-2.86-r7 (16 Jul 2007)

  16 Jul 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +sysvinit-2.86-r7.ebuild:
  Give /sbin/halt CAP_NET_ADMIN and CLSM_PRIV_NETOTHER through 
  veriexec, to stop ifdown complaining...

* sysvinit-2.86-r6 (24 May 2007)

  24 May 2007; EADS D&S <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +files/inittab.clip-r6, sysvinit-2.86-r6.ebuild:
  minor upgrade : boot sequence is now SYSINIT => BOOT => +NONETWORK => DEFAULT

  30 Jan 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  sysvinit-2.86-r5.ebuild:
  Make previous patch depend on USE clip-lsm, to be coherent with
  other ebuilds. Add verictl support, create an entry authorizing
  CAP_SYS_BOOT on /sbin/halt.
  
  22 Jan 2007; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +files/sysvinit-2.86-clip-cap_inh.patch, sysvinit-2.86-r5.ebuild:
  Add a patch to raise init's cap_inheritable to CAP_FULL - CAP_SETPCAP
  when going to runlevel 0 or 6, so we can then USE umount, cryptsetup, 
  etc as needed to cleanly halt the system. TODO : refine, respect 
  cap-bound, etc.
  
  18 Sep 2006; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +files/inittab.clip, sysvinit-2.86-r5.ebuild:
  Add USE clip and clip-specific inittab. For now, the only difference
  is that the xdm entry is moved to follow the move to /usr/local/etc/X11.

* sysvinit-2.86-r5 (29 Aug 2006)

  29 Aug 2006; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  sysvinit-2.86-r5.ebuild:
  Initial CLIP import. Add USE hardened, if set, do not apply the 
  ${P}-POSIX-1003.1e.patch, that breaks cap-bound. Will report upstream.
